# SegmentedButton

Use segmented buttons to allow users to select from a group of mutually exclusive options.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/segmented-button
```

```tsx
import { SegmentedButton } from '@ids-ts/segmented-button';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `ariaLabel` | `string` | Yes | The aria-label to define the purpose of the group of the buttons |
| `buttonInfos` | `ButtonInterface[]` | Yes | Type providing information for each button. See ButtonInterface for more information. |
| `size` | `'standard' \| 'mini'` | No | Size variant. Defaults to `'standard'`. |
| `align` | `'center' \| 'right' \| 'left'` | No | Alignment of the button group. Defaults to `'left'`. |
| `className` | `string` | No | Custom classes to be added to the segmented button's HTML <section>. |
| `label` | `string` | Yes | Label for button. |
| `selected` | `boolean` | Yes | The selected button segment; only one segment should be set as a selected. |
| `content` | `ReactNode` | No | A component or string shown underneath the segmented button. |
| `buttonAriaLabel` | `string` | No | The aria-label for a single segmented button. |
| `onClick` | `React.ReactEventHandler<HTMLButtonElement>` | No | Called when a single button is clicked. |
| `onKeyDown` | `React.KeyboardEventHandler<HTMLButtonElement>` | No | A callback to be fired when a single button has a key pressed on it. |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface SegmentedButtonProps extends Themeable {
  /** The aria-label to define the purpose of the group of the buttons */
  ariaLabel: string;

  /** Type providing information for each button. See ButtonInterface for more information. */
  buttonInfos: ButtonInterface[];

  /** Type of button:'standard' or 'mini'
   *
   * @default 'standard'
   */
  buttonType?: 'standard' | 'mini';

  /** The segmented button's position inside the container:'center','right' or 'left'
   *
   * @default 'left'
   */
  buttonPosition?: 'center' | 'right' | 'left';

  /** Custom classes to be added to the segmented button's HTML <section>. */
  className?: string;
}

export interface ButtonInterface {
  /** Label for button. */
  label: string;

  /** The selected button segment; only one segment should be set as a selected. */
  selected: boolean;

  /** A component or string shown underneath the segmented button. */
  content?: ReactNode;

  /** The aria-label for a single segmented button. */
  buttonAriaLabel?: string;

  /** A callback to be fired when a single button is clicked. */
  onClick?:
    | React.ReactEventHandler<HTMLButtonElement>
    | React.MouseEventHandler<HTMLButtonElement>;

  /** A callback to be fired when a single button has a key pressed on it. */
  onKeyDown?: React.KeyboardEventHandler<HTMLButtonElement>;
}
```

</details>

